<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3690&amp;p=28216#p28216"><![CDATA[
I guess FF5 uses the old SHVC-1B3M board (I have Secret of Mana (J) which also uses this borard, whent the newer Secret of Mana (E) uses SHVC-1J3M).<br />The main difference is that a 74-139 decoder is used instead of a MAD-1. Because half of the 139 is already used to decode SRAM, maye the other half can be used to decode ROMs ??<br /><br />EDIT : Yes, I can confirm half of the 74LS139 is unused on the SHVC-1B3M-01 board. I guess you'd have to disconnect the unused inputs for either GND or VCC where they're tied tough.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Nov 13, 2007 9:56 am</p><hr />
